question: John Constantine/Balthazar???
answer:
JOHNNY BOI.

Who cooks normally?

I’ve said it before, I’ll say it again: John Constantine cannot cook. And Balthazar’s a supernatural being, he doesn’t even NEED to eat. When John’s hungry, they order takeout, or try (and fail) not to cause a scene at a restaurant.

How often do they fight?

John’s got some holy water lying around so Balthazar better not try SHIT. After a big argument, he’ll spray it on himself like cologne so Balthazar can’t touch him. He’s petty like that - he’d much rather use his knowledge of the occult to solve arguments than actually TALK through their feelings.

What do they do when they’re away from each other?

Balthazar parties hard with his demon pals. John goes to nightclubs as well, but doesn’t enjoy himself. He chews a bunch of gum to curb his nicotine cravings, too.

Nicknames for each other?

I mean, “Johnny Boy”, first of all. Also, “Bally”. Sometimes they’ll just call one another “Demon” and “Exorcist”, especially when they’re in a bad mood.

Who is more likely to pay for dinner?

Neither. Johnny Boy’s broke af, and Balthazar objects to having to pay for anything when he can just as easily use his powers of manipulation to make the waiter think he’s paid already. John knows it’s wrong, but he ain’t complaining.

Who steals the covers at night?

John. Balthazar isn’t in touch with his corporeal form enough to care about the cold. He also doesn’t particularly like to sleep anyway. When you’re a demon, the night is for lurking, not for sleeping. He’s sure as hell not going to be unconscious for the best part of the day.

What would they get each other for gifts?

Balthazar gets John a pocket watch to remind him that his mortal life is inevitably finite. John actually doesn’t mind, because it’s a pretty cool-looking watch. He gets Balthazar a crucifix. Balthazar doesn’t find it amusing.

Who remembers things?

Balthazar’s fucking ancient. He remembers all. John can’t even remember where he left his keys.

Who cusses more?

Trust John Fucking Constantine to out-swear a literal demon.

What would they do if the other one was hurt?

Balthazar doesn’t get hurt, and if he did, it would probably be because of John to begin with. Needless to say, Balthazar doesn’t have the best bedside manner - he mostly taunts John about the fragility of his human form. John tells him to fuck off and bother someone else for a while.

Who kissed who first?

Balthazar, in an attempt to freak John out. Little did he know how much John would be into it.

Who made the first move?

Again, Balthazar - John’s a disaster who doesn’t know how to initiate things.

Who started the relationship?

There never really was a “start” to the relationship. Balthazar just won’t leave John alone, and John supposes that’s something like having a partner. Sort of.
